      • hasIdentity

        public boolean hasIdentity()
        Description copied from interface: Composite
        Determine whether a Composite instance is a managed object. Being managed means that hashCode() and equals() operate on the object instance itself rather than the instance's members. This means that the instance can be tracked where it is important to ensure that multiple threads are dealing with physically the same object.

        Most Composite implementations will return false with identity semantics being bestowed by suitable decorator. Note that

      • getPath

        public Any getPath(Any to)
        Description copied from interface: Composite
        Return the full path to this node from to If to is null then the path to the root of the process's node space is returned. If to (or the root node if this is not in the node space) cannot be found then null is returned.

        Optional operation. Only supported by implementations that know their parent and name in the hierarchy.

        Specified by:
        getPath in interface Composite
        Parameters:
        to - The node to stop at as the upward traversal is performed or the root (which must be known) is null.
        Returns:
        path to this node from to or the known root, or null if the traversal is unsuccessful or this implementation does not support the operation.
